Installing Alleviam
*******************

This guide will tell you how to install the Alleviam buildout for the host
cancer.jpl.nasa.gov.  This host is the *master* Alleviam server.  Alleviam is
built on Monit_, a utility for monitoring a the health of and network services
provided by a single Unix system as well as network services of remote Unix
systems.


Quick Installation
==================

Hate reading and need excitement?  Try the following:

1. Run: ``/usr/local/python-2.4.4/bin/python2.4 bootstrap.py -dc operations.cfg``
2. Run: ``bin/buildout -c operations.cfg``
3. Run: ``sudo bin/buildout -c operations.cfg install permissions``
4. Add to ``/usr/local/apache2/conf/edrn.conf``: ``Include /usr/local/alleviam/parts/alleviam-config/httpd.cfg``
5. Copy ``parts/alleviam-config/alleviam`` to ``/etc/init.d``
6. Run: ``chkconfig --add alleviam``
7. Run: ``service httpd restart``
8. Run: ``service alleviam start``


Requirements
============

python >= 2.4
zlib 1.2; quite standard these days
png; also quite standard (sudo apt-get install libpng12-dev)
libjpeg; optional on some systems
freetype2; optional on some systems (sudo apt-get install libfreetype6-dev)
libperl5.10; perl runtime might only be present, need shared perl lib too (install libperl-dev, libperl5.10)
fontconfig; sudo apt-get install libfontconfig1-dev
libldap2-dev
apache2
libxml2-dev
libxslt-dev

